.TH OB-HEARTBEAT 8 "December 2025" "open-bastion 0.1.0" "System Administration"
.SH NAME
ob-heartbeat \- Send heartbeat to LemonLDAP::NG server
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ob-heartbeat
.RI [ OPTIONS ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B ob-heartbeat
sends a heartbeat signal to the LemonLDAP::NG server to report that this
server is still active and using PAM authentication.
.PP
The heartbeat allows administrators to monitor enrolled servers and detect
"ghost" servers that have uninstalled the PAM module without proper unenrollment.
.PP
This script is typically run by a systemd timer (ob-heartbeat.timer)
every 5 minutes.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-c ", " \-\-config " " \fIFILE\fR
Read settings from config file. Default: /etc/open-bastion/openbastion.conf
.TP
.BR \-t ", " \-\-token\-file " " \fIFILE\fR
Server token file. Default: /etc/open-bastion/token
.TP
.BR \-k ", " \-\-insecure
Skip SSL certificate verification.
.TP
.BR \-q ", " \-\-quiet
Quiet mode (less output).
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Show help message and exit.
.TP
.BR \-V ", " \-\-version
Show version and exit.
.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
Send a heartbeat manually:
.RS
.nf
sudo ob-heartbeat
.fi
.RE
.PP
Check heartbeat timer status:
.RS
.nf
systemctl status ob-heartbeat.timer
.fi
.RE
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /etc/open-bastion/openbastion.conf
Main configuration file for the PAM module.
.TP
.I /etc/open-bastion/token
Server token file containing access and refresh tokens.
.TP
.I /var/lib/open-bastion/
Directory for storing statistics and state.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Heartbeat sent successfully.
.TP
.B 1
Heartbeat failed (missing token, network error, etc.)
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR ob-enroll (8),
.BR pam_openbastion (8),
.BR systemd.timer (5)
.PP
